This module introduces some ways of representing data using examples from MLB, the NBA and Indian Premier League. 
MLB data is used to analyze the spatial distribution of different hits. 
NBA data is used to generate heatmaps to illustrate the different ways in which players contribute. 
IPL data is used to show how team performances can be compared graphically.

Learning Objectives
  Identify ways to visualize sports data
  Utilize Matplotlib to generate plots to describe the relationship between variables
  Develop strategies for telling stories about the data visually
